Results.ReviewText: I love ground coffee and speciality drinks, but I use this at home because it has a rich enough taste for me. My mother does not like coffee, but she drinks this because its not bitter. So it keeps everyone happy! Its also good for baking as the freeze dried granules melt instantly and don't have the powdery feel of cheap brands.
Results.Title: Gold Standard

Results.ReviewText: This is the only instant coffee we drink, and I buy a jar every week. glad to say the quality and taste are as good as they have always been. One slight criticism of the new packaging, the smooth sides of the new glass jar look very attractive but they make the jar harder to pick up and hold than the curved sides of the old jar.
Results.Title: Quality and taste as good as ever.

Results.ReviewText: I used to by a cheaper brand of "Gold" coffee and was satisfied with what I knew. However, after treating myself to a jar of Nescafe Gold Blend, I have realised that all coffee is not that same. Nescafe has a distinctly smoother, velvety taste and without milk, it is not bitter. I now only Have Nescafe Gold blend in my kitchen!!
Results.Title: Simply The BEST!

Results.ReviewText: As good as it gets for an instant coffee! New recipe attempts to replicate the taste and aroma of real coffee to tempt us non instant coffee drinkers to buy some! Guess what? It worked and I now have a jar at home which was unthinkable not long ago! I give it 3 stars which is a higher rating than i have given some real coffees.
Results.Title: the best instant coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for getting in touch & leaving your thoughts on the new recipe. We really value your feedback & will be passing it to the wider team.

Results.ReviewText: I have been a fan of Gold Blend for more years than I care to remember but are so disappointed with the new formulation.  The simulated 'Barista' experience of sludge in the bottom of the drink is like a plastic imitation of the real thing. Please revert to the original  -  I am very much the ' ain't broke don't fix it' camp.
Results.Title: New style packaging disguises an inferior product

Results.ReviewText: This is a coffee that my late parents enjoyed, we enjoy and grown up children enjoy. And we stick with it as we moved across nine countries and sometimes we had to ask friends to buy and bring. It epitomises ' smell the coffee' in a nice way. A cup when I wake up, once in the afternoon and twenty minutes before a long drive.
Results.Title: A bridge across the generational gap

Results.ReviewText: I have always bought this Nescafé version because I'm not keen on really strong coffee but this one has a rich smith taste without tasting bitter or too strong . I have tried many cheaper brands but always go back to this one because I think it is the best quality and flavour for the price . Please don't change the recipe.
Results.Title: Love the Gold title it' arttracts me!

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for taking the time to share your thoughts with us. Your feedback has been noted and passed forward to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: By adding micro ground coffee you have ruined the taste and texture of this coffee. We have been using this product for very many years but unless you improve it (revert to the original blend and mixture) we will buy an alternative. All our friends well the same as we do. Please take note and read reviews from other sites.
Results.Title: What a Huge mistake

Results.ReviewText:
Just run out of my Nescafe Gold Blend at home and this new stuff is bland with a strange aftertaste. Nowhere near as great as it used to be.
I particularly do not like the sediment it leaves in the cup, an obvious attempt to make it seem more like real coffee but without the taste.

Poor imitation of what it once was.
Results.Title: Terrible, no better than supermarket own brand now

Results.ReviewText: Can only echo what dozens have people have said - the new Gold Blend is horrid. I too have drunk Gold Blend for years and years and have never bought anything else. Now I am scratching about with Lavazza and Percol (both ok-ish). Will try Aldi’s version based on an earlier review. Please please change it back Nescafé!!!!
Results.Title: Please please change it back Nescafé!!!!

Results.ReviewText: Having purchased Gold Blend for 20+ years, am now looking for a replacement brand after the recent reformulation.  It has ruined a perfectly good product.  I find it to be slightly more bitter and leaves a gritty residue in the bottom of the cup, which I dislike. Please go back to the original or I will not buy it again.
Results.Title: Not nice since the repackaging.

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for taking the time & leaving your feedback! Although it saddens us to hear you're unhappy, we appreciate you letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: The new jar is very stylish, the "improved" Gold Blend coffee is vile. Nasty bitter taste and sludge at the bottom of the cup.  I would have given this NO stars if I could have.  I won't be buying this again, unfortunately I bought two jars of the stuff, and it's all going in the bin. Bring back the original Gold Blend!
Results.Title: Gutted

Results.ReviewText: Our family have used Nescafé Gold Blend coffee for more years than I can remember, but no more, as it has become far too expensive for us as a retired couple, with one daughter still at home. Pity because we both loved Gold blend and never before have we considered buying a less than satisfactory product, but we do now!
Results.Title: Now too expensive

Results.ReviewText: Do you know that feeling when someone asks, 'would you like a coffee?' and you say  'Yes' then think 'oh. I wonder what brand they use.'  there is nothing worse than a bad coffee that is too bitter or just smells and tastes bland. Nescafe Gold Blend is a quality everyday coffee, reliable and drinkable at every occasion.
Results.Title: Solid Reliable Good Coffee

Results.ReviewText: This is my number one, 1st choice coffee. It tastes better than any of the coffees I have bought at the big Coffee Outlets. You definitely don't need an expensive coffee machine when all you need is hot water just off the boil and a reasonable heaped teaspoon of this delicious coffee and a splash of milk. Hey presto!
Results.Title: 1st Choice

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk Gold Blend for years and is the only coffee I will drink but no longer. The recent changes to the blend make it taste terrible and leaves sludge at bottom of cup. If I wanted barista style coffee I would buy barista style coffee. Please go back to old recipe. Now I will be changing to a different coffee
Results.Title: Not happy with change to blend

I do not feel the quality of the coffee is nearly as good as it used to be.  The taste and smell of the coffee once made is not nearly as enticing as it used to be and i no longer savour my coffee as i did.
Results.Title: Coffee has changed

Results.ReviewText: I love this coffee sooo much because I have to drink black coffee. As adding milk makes me feel ill. This has a very lovely. Aroma and fantastic flavour with no horrible after taste like other brands of coffee I don't drink any other coffee this is the one I am sticking too thanks for making such a fantastic coffeex
Results.Title: I love this coffee soooo much

Results.ReviewText: we tried this a few weeks ago as it was on offer in our local supermarket and i am so glad we did! a perfect companion for our afternoon cake, the taste is so smooth, i prefer mine quite milky but the taste still came through superbly. The good thing is you dont have to use a lot so the jar will last us a few weeks.
Results.Title: lovely blend

Results.ReviewText: Bought this particular brand of coffee as it's one I've grown up with and know it's the taste I love, the smell and feeling you get when piercing the foil for the first time and that first sip on a morning gives me that little kick I need to start my day at work, it's not over priced and every cup makes me glow....
Results.Title: Really is the better way to start the day

Results.ReviewText: This is the only coffee to drink. It is not bitter. It has the best flavor any coffee can have without being, to strong, but not too mild. I always look at the price for the refill pack, as i like the idea of not buying a jar every time. But sometimes the price per 100gms is cheaper by the jar than the refill pack.
Results.Title: simply the best

Results.ReviewText: I have bought this coffee for the last four years as an alternative to coffee beans to drink in the evening. I found the coffee is just as delicious as drinking fresh coffee. The quality is consistently excellent and good value for money and I have served this as iced coffee in the summer. This was delicious too
Results.Title: Excellent value in taste and for your money

Results.ReviewText: I will never ever change my brand of coffee no matter if you gave it away for free!!  I love to sit for 5 minutes after a manic morning and pour myself a cup of Nescafe Gold Blend. I love the smooth taste and aroma and it just makes the whole world feel so much better!!  Thank you Nescafe for keeping me sane!! X
Results.Title: Little piece of heaven in a jar!!

Results.ReviewText: Why have you ruined what was a great cup of coffee???  The sludge in the bottom of the cup is awful and now I only drink half a cup as I do not want to think that I am ingesting the sludge.  If I wanted a proper barista style coffee, I would buy one.  Now I have to find an alternative to my beloved Gold Blend.
Results.Title: You have ruined my morning coffee!

Results.ReviewText: Great instant coffee as good as any from a cafe. It is so smooth and a consistent taste absent in others. My favourite coffee whether it is black, white or I'm treating myself with some cream.A great way to start the day and also a great base if you like to make festive coffees (i.e. Irish or Baileys coffee)
Results.Title: A definite winner

Results.ReviewText: Myself and wife are nescafe addicts and our morning isn't complete without a cup of nescafe gold. I have to admit we tried other brands over the years -only out of curiosity - but none have managed to reach our taste buds. I love the new packiging  but my wife doesn't!! she is still in love with the old one.
Results.Title: a daily must!

Results.ReviewText: I just love the rich  taste ,the smell is so inviting, I drink my coffee black with no sugar and the amount of friends and colleagues that ask what I'm drinking because it smells so nice ,even had people who have said "I don't like coffee but that smells lovely", could not go through the day with out a cup
Results.Title: Rich taste

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend has been my go-to coffee since Tony and Sharon started their slow-burning romance. In fact, my relationship with Gold Blend has lasted longer than any boyfriend. It's been there for me through bad times and good. A true nugget to keep in your cupboards. (the coffee- not the boyfriend)
Results.Title: Rich taste and smooth too

Results.ReviewText: I love this coffee, the aroma is tantalizing, the taste rewarding; I can drink it strong or less strong.  It's my wake up drink, my mid morning drink, my relaxing with friends drink, my after lunch and after dinner drink.  It is the quality I expect from Nescafe.  Value for money, an all round pleasure.
Results.Title: Silky and smooth

Results.ReviewText: I have used Gold Blend for many years and love it, however the new jar is not very good if you have small hands, the waisted jar was far easier to hold.  As we now have many ladies in this Country with small hands, could the designer please remember this for any future changes.  The new coffee is great!
Results.Title: Wonderful coffee but...
